beer.beer_description: A beer that’s fresh and crushable. Classic tropical aromas from Mosaic Cryo and Galaxy hops give sticky over ripe mango, apricot and passion fruit flavours. Citra in the whirlpool and Bru-1 in the dry goo add citrus and fresh zesty pineapple to balance. Lighter bodied than most hazy pales to cut back on perceived sweetness and create a beer you can drink over and over again.

items.checkin_comment: So many complex flavours!! Love this one.

items.badge_description: Thanks for staying at home, and checking in with Untappd! It allows us to stay connected to a community of beer lovers, just like you, even if we can't be in the same physical location. From our home to yours, cheers and stay safe!

Want to enjoy a day of brews, but need to keep your wits sharp? There are plenty of delicious brews under 5% for you to sip on throughout the day. That's 15 different beers with an ABV of 5% and lower. Try 5 more for Level 4!

There's beer in them thar hills! You're setting off on your journey through the world of beer, but be sure to take a little time to get to know each brewery as you go. That's a beer from 25 different breweries. Try 5 more for Level 6!
Get out there and raise a ruckus with your favorite Amber or Red Ale! That's 10 different amber or red beers. Try 5 more for Level 3!
Do you come from the land down under, where beer does flow, and men chunder? That's at least 215 different beers from Australia. Try 5 more for Level 44.

It's time to give bottle shops some love by adding them as your purchased location. That's 35 check-ins with a purchased location! Tag 5 more to get to Level 8. Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

Canning is all the rage and it's not hard to see why - travels well, more environmentally friendly, and no need to carry your bottle opener. That's 155 checkins with the serving style of Can. Try 5 more for Level 32! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

beer.beer_description: Everything you could ever need from a New England Style IPA. A big pillowy mouth feel provided by a huge dose of both Voyager Malted Oats and Flaked Oats while Chit and Wheat malt provide that final dose of protein heavy malts. This is all layered on top of Voyager Atlas Malt, as a base. All the hopping starts in the whirlpool with Citra Cryo, El Dorado Cryo and Strata, for big citrus, tropical fruits and dank flavours. The addition of Riwaka and Spectrum Citra in the dry hop take the aroma to new levels with sweet tropical citrus fruits. Fermented with New England style yeast, this is a true beer lover’s delight.

A beer that’s fresh and crushable. Classic tropical aromas from Mosaic Cryo and Galaxy hops give sticky over ripe mango, apricot and passion fruit flavours. Citra in the whirlpool and Bru-1 in the dry goo add citrus and fresh zesty pineapple to balance. Lighter bodied than most hazy pales to cut back on perceived sweetness and create a beer you can drink over and over again.

Everything you could ever need from a New England Style IPA. A big pillowy mouth feel provided by a huge dose of both Voyager Malted Oats and Flaked Oats while Chit and Wheat malt provide that final dose of protein heavy malts. This is all layered on top of Voyager Atlas Malt, as a base. All the hopping starts in the whirlpool with Citra Cryo, El Dorado Cryo and Strata, for big citrus, tropical fruits and dank flavours. The addition of Riwaka and Spectrum Citra in the dry hop take the aroma to new levels with sweet tropical citrus fruits. Fermented with New England style yeast, this is a true beer lover’s delight.

Brewed in the style of a west coast IPA with a healthy hit of clean bitterness, Strata, Amarillo and Ekuanot hops give this beer some dank resinous flavour, and citrus fruits aroma, balanced with some earthy notes from Loral. This beer is backed up with a malt bill of Munich, Wheat and Chit to provide body and balance. Extra colour, chewiness and complexity comes from Voyager Voodoo Schooner Malt.

A dark lager, with subtle notes of fresh roasted coffee, dark chocolate balanced with sweet plum and raisin. These flavours are derived from Voyager Voodoo Schooner, Midnight Wheat and Chocolate Malt, a smidge of Loral and Hallertau Tradition give the perfect floral, earthy aroma this black beer needs. Clean cold ferment on lager yeast creates the light body and easy drinking nature of this beer.
Dry, tart, lightly hopped for balance.
Super light and crisp lager. subtle floral, citrus and noble flavours, light malty sweetness derived from voyager schooner malt. A true craft lager that’s more normal.

A mid strength beer that punches well above its weight. A bold malt bill provides a full mouthfeel using wheat, malted oats and Voyager Schooner Malt, with no shortage ofclean bitterness and aroma to round out. Citra and El Dorado, provide bright citrus and stone fruit flavours along with Ella which provides a floral and spicy balance.

A Hazy style IPA loaded with oats for a creamy, silky smooth body. Hops provide all the tropical stone fruit aromas as well as the addition of a roasted peach puree for some caramelised sweetness and an extra fruity punch. Millions of peaches, peaches for me.

A full bodied hazy pale with low bitterness and simple malt bill allow the true aroma of Galaxy and Mosaic. Dry hopped during the ferment allows bio-transformation to occur where yeast and hops interact to create a more complex hop aroma and hazy finished beer.

Kettle soured Berliner Weisse, forms the base for this fruited sour. Topaz hops are used for light bittering and subtle fruity notes. The addition of Blood Orange and Rosemary after ferment create a complex refreshing sour beer that will quench any thirst. Our chef created the extract in house.

A simple malt profile of Voyager Atlas, Munich, Malted Oats and Voyager Voodoo Schooner gives this big beer the easy drinking feeling. Loaded with the heavy hitting North American Centennial, Mosaic, Ekuanot and Citra Hops this beer has the bitterness and aroma of Pine, Citrus and Melon that a big double IPA needs. Aussie Vic Secret is used during boil for an added tangy punch. Everything there is to love about an IPA, doubled.
Well balanced hop and malt feel. Crisp and full flavor with potential to creep at 6.8 %
Thick, strong, robust.
